---
import LessonLayout from '../../layouts/LessonLayout.astro';
---
<LessonLayout
  title="What is a Robot?"
  track="little-explorers"
  week={1}
  phase="Phase 1: Unplugged"
  duration="30 min"
  emoji="🤔"
  objective="Discover that robots are machines that follow instructions"
>
  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-explorer-700 mb-3">🎯 Learning Objective</h2>
    <p class="bg-explorer-50 border-l-4 border-explorer-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl text-gray-700">
      By the end of this session, your child will be able to say what a robot is, name 2–3 robots they know, and understand that robots follow instructions from people.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">🛠️ Materials</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Paper and crayons</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ A toy robot or robot picture book (optional)</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Yourself as the "human robot"!</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📋 Activity Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold">Robot Hunt (5 min)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">Look around the house together. Can you find anything that does a job automatically? Washing machine, dishwasher, vacuum robot? Talk about how each one follows instructions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold">Be a Robot! (10 min)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">Take turns being the "robot" and the "programmer." The programmer gives ONE instruction at a time: "Take one step forward." "Raise your right arm." The robot follows exactly — no thinking ahead!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold">Draw Your Dream Robot (10 min)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">Ask your child: "If you could have any robot helper, what would it do?" Draw it together. Label its special powers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold">Wrap Up (5 min)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">Hang the drawing somewhere visible. Say together: "A robot is a machine that follows instructions!"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💬 Reflection Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "What's your favourite robot from a story or show?"</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "What would happen if a robot didn't follow instructions?"</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "What would YOUR robot be called?"</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">👪 Parent Tips</h2>
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-5 space-y-2 text-gray-700">
      <p>💡 Keep the "be a robot" game fun — it's okay to be silly! Falling over from a vague instruction teaches that <strong>precision matters</strong>.</p>
      <p>💡 If your child has seen R2-D2, WALL-E, or Baymax, those are great conversation starters.</p>
      <p>💡 Don't worry about technical accuracy at this stage — nurture curiosity and wonder.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LessonLayout>
